# =============================================================================
# Suricata Global Thresholds and Suppressions
# =============================================================================
# Suppress an alert for a specific source IP:
#   suppress gen_id 1, sig_id <SID>, track by_src, ip <IP>
#
# Suppress an alert network-wide:
#   suppress gen_id 1, sig_id <SID>
#
# Rate-limit a noisy rule to 1 alert per 60s per source:
#   event_filter gen_id 1, sig_id <SID>, type limit, track by_src, count 1, seconds 60
# =============================================================================

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Known-good managed devices — suppress informational RMM/MDM alerts
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Daughter's school Chromebook (192.168.10.129, dc:56:7b:06:72:d9)
# School IT manages this device via NinjaRMM — agent connections are expected
suppress gen_id 1, sig_id 2066841, track by_src, ip 192.168.10.129
